<BODY LANG="en-US" DIR="LTR">
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=4 STYLE="font-size: 16pt"><B>GASSST
: Global Alignment Short Sequence Search Tool</B></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=4>GASSST
is a free software distributed under the terms of the</FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><A HREF="http://www.cecill.info/licences/Licence_CeCILL_V2-en.html"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=4>CECILL
version 2 License</FONT></FONT></A></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=3>GASSST
article is now <A HREF="http://bioinformatics.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/btq485?ijkey=f5zH80QsuCqixRH&amp;keytype=ref">available!</A></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #280099; page-break-before: auto; page-break-after: auto">
<FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=5 STYLE="font-size: 20pt"><B>Overview</B></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<UL>
	<LI><P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>GASSST
	finds global alignments of short DNA sequences against large DNA
	banks.</FONT></FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>GASSST
	strong point is its ability to perform fast gapped alignments. </FONT></FONT>
	</P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>It
	works well for both short and longer reads. It currently has been
	tested for reads up to 500bp.</FONT></FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>The
	software is freely available for download under the CECILL version 2
	License.</FONT></FONT></P>
</UL>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2><B>Usage
example :</B></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; font-weight: medium"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>For
alignments with 90 % similarity minimum</FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; font-weight: medium"><FONT FACE="Courier, monospace"><FONT SIZE=2>Gassst
-d bank.fasta -i query.fasta -o results -p 90</FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; font-weight: medium"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>Then
call &quot;gassst_to_sam&quot; if you want to convert output to SAM
format : </FONT></FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; font-weight: medium"><FONT FACE="Courier, monospace"><FONT SIZE=2>./gassst_to_sam
results results.sam</FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; font-weight: medium"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>The
program takes as inputs 2 banks in FASTA format :</FONT></FONT></P>
<UL>
	<LI><P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; font-weight: medium"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>bank_file
	: a collection of DNA sequences of any length (from short EST
	sequence to full genome).</FONT></FONT></P>
	<LI><P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; font-weight: medium"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2>query
	file : a collection of very short DNA sequences.</FONT></FONT></P>
</UL>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=2><SPAN STYLE="font-weight: medium">For
the complete list of options, see the <A HREF="http://www.irisa.fr/symbiose/projects/gassst/README">readme
file.</A></SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-left: 0.29in; margin-bottom: 0in"><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0in; background: #280099"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><FONT FACE="arial, sans-serif"><FONT SIZE=5 STYLE="font-size: 20pt"><B>Download</B></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
